7 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
8 // ----
9 // This pass tries to fuse DS instructions with close by immediate offsets. ----
10 // This will fuse operations such as ----
11 // ds_read_b32 v0, v2 offset:16 ----
12 // ds_read_b32 v1, v2 offset:32 ----
13 // ==> ----
14 // ds_read2_b32 v[0:1], v2, offset0:4 offset1:8 ----
15 // ----
16 // The same is done for certain SMEM and VMEM opcodes, e.g.: ----
17 // s_buffer_load_dword s4, s[0:3], 4 ----
18 // s_buffer_load_dword s5, s[0:3], 8 ----
19 // ==> ----
20 // s_buffer_load_dwordx2 s[4:5], s[0:3], 4 ----
21 // ----
22 // This pass also tries to promote constant offset to the immediate by ----
23 // adjusting the base. It tries to use a base from the nearby instructions that ----
24 // allows it to have a 13bit constant offset and then promotes the 13bit offset ----
25 // to the immediate. ----
26 // E.g. ----
27 // s_movk_i32 s0, 0x1800 ----
28 // v_add_co_u32_e32 v0, vcc, s0, v2 ----
29 // v_addc_co_u32_e32 v1, vcc, 0, v6, vcc ----
30 // ----
31 // s_movk_i32 s0, 0x1000 ----
32 // v_add_co_u32_e32 v5, vcc, s0, v2 ----
33 // v_addc_co_u32_e32 v6, vcc, 0, v6, vcc ----
34 // global_load_dwordx2 v[5:6], v[5:6], off ----
35 // global_load_dwordx2 v[0:1], v[0:1], off ----
36 // => ----
37 // s_movk_i32 s0, 0x1000 ----
38 // v_add_co_u32_e32 v5, vcc, s0, v2 ----
39 // v_addc_co_u32_e32 v6, vcc, 0, v6, vcc ----
40 // global_load_dwordx2 v[5:6], v[5:6], off ----
41 // global_load_dwordx2 v[0:1], v[5:6], off offset:2048 ----
42 // ----
43 // Future improvements: ----
44 // ----
45 // - This is currently missing stores of constants because loading ----
46 // the constant into the data register is placed between the stores, although ----
47 // this is arguably a scheduling problem. ----
48 // ----
49 // - Live interval recomputing seems inefficient. This currently only matches ----
50 // one pair, and recomputes live intervals and moves on to the next pair. It ----
51 // would be better to compute a list of all merges that need to occur. ----
52 // ----
53 // - With a list of instructions to process, we can also merge more. If a ----
54 // cluster of loads have offsets that are too large to fit in the 8-bit ----
55 // offsets, but are close enough to fit in the 8 bits, we can add to the base ----
56 // pointer and use the new reduced offsets. ----
57 // ----
58 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
59 ----

108 struct CombineInfo { ----
109 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I; ----
110 unsigned EltSize; ----
111 unsigned Offset; ----
112 unsigned Width; ----
113 unsigned Format; ----
114 unsigned BaseOff; ----
115 unsigned DMask; ----
116 InstClassEnum InstClass; ----
117 unsigned CPol = 0; ----

120 int AddrIdx[MaxAddressRegs]; ----
121 const MachineOperand *AddrReg[MaxAddressRegs]; ----
122 unsigned NumAddresses; ----
123 unsigned Order; ----
124 ----
125 bool hasSameBaseAddress(const CombineInfo &CI) { 0
126 if (NumAddresses != CI.NumAddresses) 0
127 return false; 0
128 ----
129 const MachineInstr &MI = *CI.I; 0
130 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumAddresses; i++) { 0
131 const MachineOperand &AddrRegNext = MI.getOperand(AddrIdx[i]); 0
132 ----
133 if (AddrReg[i]->isImm() || AddrRegNext.isImm()) { 0
134 if (AddrReg[i]->isImm() != AddrRegNext.isImm() || 0
135 AddrReg[i]->getImm() != AddrRegNext.getImm()) { 0
136 return false; 0
137 } ----
138 continue; 0
139 } ----
140 ----
141 // Check same base pointer. Be careful of subregisters, which can occur ----
142 // with vectors of pointers. ----
143 if (AddrReg[i]->getReg() != AddrRegNext.getReg() || 0
144 AddrReg[i]->getSubReg() != AddrRegNext.getSubReg()) { 0
145 return false; 0
146 } ----
147 } ----
148 return true; 0
149 } ----
150 ----
151 bool hasMergeableAddress(const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI) { 0
152 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumAddresses; ++i) { 0
153 const MachineOperand *AddrOp = AddrReg[i]; 0
154 // Immediates are always OK. ----
155 if (AddrOp->isImm()) 0
156 continue; 0
157 ----
158 // Don't try to merge addresses that aren't either immediates or registers. ----
159 // TODO: Should be possible to merge FrameIndexes and maybe some other ----
160 // non-register ----
161 if (!AddrOp->isReg()) 0
162 return false; 0
163 ----
164 // TODO: We should be able to merge physical reg addresses. ----
165 if (AddrOp->getReg().isPhysical()) 0
166 return false; 0
167 ----
168 // If an address has only one use then there will be no other ----
169 // instructions with the same address, so we can't merge this one. ----
170 if (MRI.hasOneNonDBGUse(AddrOp->getReg())) 0
171 return false; 0
172 } ----
173 return true; 0
174 } ----
175 ----
176 void setMI(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI, const SILoadStoreOptimizer &LSO); ----
177 ----
178 // Compare by pointer order. ----
179 bool operator<(const CombineInfo& Other) const { 0
180 return (InstClass == MIMG) ? DMask < Other.DMask : Offset < Other.Offset; 0
181 } ----
182 }; ----

326 return llvm::popcount(DMaskImm); 0

390 static InstClassEnum getInstClass(unsigned Opc, const SIInstrInfo &TII) { 0
391 switch (Opc) { 0
392 default: 0
393 if (TII.isMUBUF(Opc)) { 0
394 switch (AMDGPU::getMUBUFBaseOpcode(Opc)) { 0
395 default: 0
396 return UNKNOWN; 0
397 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_OFFEN: 0
398 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_OFFEN_exact: ----
399 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_OFFSET: ----
400 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_OFFSET_exact: ----
401 return BUFFER_LOAD; 0
402 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_STORE_DWORD_OFFEN: 0
403 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_STORE_DWORD_OFFEN_exact: ----
404 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_STORE_DWORD_OFFSET: ----
405 case AMDGPU::BUFFER_STORE_DWORD_OFFSET_exact: ----
406 return BUFFER_STORE; 0
407 } ----
408 } ----
409 if (TII.isMIMG(Opc)) { 0
410 // Ignore instructions encoded without vaddr. ----
411 if (!AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr) && 0
412 !AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0)) 0
413 return UNKNOWN; 0
414 // Ignore BVH instructions ----
415 if (AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcode(Opc)->BVH) 0
416 return UNKNOWN; 0
417 // TODO: Support IMAGE_GET_RESINFO and IMAGE_GET_LOD. ----
418 if (TII.get(Opc).mayStore() || !TII.get(Opc).mayLoad() || 0
419 TII.isGather4(Opc)) 0
420 return UNKNOWN; 0
421 return MIMG; 0
422 } ----
423 if (TII.isMTBUF(Opc)) { 0
424 switch (AMDGPU::getMTBUFBaseOpcode(Opc)) { 0
425 default: 0
426 return UNKNOWN; 0
427 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_OFFEN: 0
428 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_OFFEN_exact: ----
429 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_OFFSET: ----
430 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_OFFSET_exact: ----
431 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_IDXEN: ----
432 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_IDXEN_exact: ----
433 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_BOTHEN: ----
434 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_X_BOTHEN_exact: ----
435 return TBUFFER_LOAD; 0
436 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_X_OFFEN: 0
437 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_X_OFFEN_exact: ----
438 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_X_OFFSET: ----
439 case AMDGPU::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_X_OFFSET_exact: ----
440 return TBUFFER_STORE; 0
441 } ----
442 } ----
443 return UNKNOWN; 0
444 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: 0
445 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM: ----
446 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
447 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
448 return S_BUFFER_LOAD_IMM; 0

450 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_SGPR_IMM: ----
451 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_SGPR_IMM: ----
452 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_SGPR_IMM: ----
453 return S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM; 0
454 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: 0

456 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
457 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
458 return S_LOAD_IMM; 0
459 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32: 0
460 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32_gfx9: ----
461 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64: ----
462 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64_gfx9: ----
463 return DS_READ; 0

500 /// Determines instruction subclass from opcode. Only instructions ----
501 /// of the same subclass can be merged together. The merged instruction may have ----
502 /// a different subclass but must have the same class. ----
503 static unsigned getInstSubclass(unsigned Opc, const SIInstrInfo &TII) { 0
504 switch (Opc) { 0
505 default: 0
506 if (TII.isMUBUF(Opc)) 0
507 return AMDGPU::getMUBUFBaseOpcode(Opc); 0
508 if (TII.isMIMG(Opc)) { 0
509 const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(Opc); 0
510 assert(Info); 0
511 return Info->BaseOpcode; 0
512 } ----
513 if (TII.isMTBUF(Opc)) 0
514 return AMDGPU::getMTBUFBaseOpcode(Opc); 0
515 return -1; 0
516 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32: 0
517 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32_gfx9: ----
518 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64: ----
519 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64_gfx9: ----
520 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B32: ----
521 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B32_gfx9: ----
522 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64: ----
523 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64_gfx9: ----
524 return Opc; 0
525 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: 0
526 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM: ----
527 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
528 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
529 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_IMM; 0
530 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_SGPR_IMM: 0
531 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_SGPR_IMM: ----
532 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_SGPR_IMM: ----
533 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_SGPR_IMM: ----
534 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_SGPR_IMM; 0
535 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: 0
536 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM: ----
537 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
538 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
539 return AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORD_IMM; 0
540 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORD: 0
541 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2: ----
542 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3: ----
543 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4: ----
544 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORD: ----
545 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX2: ----
546 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX3: ----
547 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX4: ----
548 return AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORD; 0
549 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORD_SADDR: 0
550 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2_SADDR: ----
551 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3_SADDR: ----
552 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4_SADDR: ----
553 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORD_SADDR; 0
554 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORD: 0
555 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2: ----
556 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3: ----
557 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4: ----
558 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORD: ----
559 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX2: ----
560 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX3: ----
561 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX4: ----
562 return AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORD; 0
563 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORD_SADDR: 0
564 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2_SADDR: ----
565 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3_SADDR: ----
566 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4_SADDR: ----
567 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORD_SADDR; 0
568 } ----
569 } ----
570 ----
571 // GLOBAL loads and stores are classified as FLAT initially. If both combined ----
572 // instructions are FLAT GLOBAL adjust the class to GLOBAL_LOAD or GLOBAL_STORE. ----
573 // If either or both instructions are non segment specific FLAT the resulting ----
574 // combined operation will be FLAT, potentially promoting one of the GLOBAL ----
575 // operations to FLAT. ----
576 // For other instructions return the original unmodified class. ----
577 InstClassEnum ----
578 SILoadStoreOptimizer::getCommonInstClass(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
579 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
580 assert(CI.InstClass == Paired.InstClass); 0
581 ----
582 if ((CI.InstClass == FLAT_LOAD || CI.InstClass == FLAT_STORE) && 0
583 SIInstrInfo::isFLATGlobal(*CI.I) && SIInstrInfo::isFLATGlobal(*Paired.I)) 0
584 return (CI.InstClass == FLAT_STORE) ? GLOBAL_STORE : GLOBAL_LOAD; 0
585 ----
586 return CI.InstClass; 0
587 } ----
588 ----
589 static AddressRegs getRegs(unsigned Opc, const SIInstrInfo &TII) { 0
590 AddressRegs Result; 0
591 ----
592 if (TII.isMUBUF(Opc)) { 0
593 if (AMDGPU::getMUBUFHasVAddr(Opc)) 0
594 Result.VAddr = true; 0
595 if (AMDGPU::getMUBUFHasSrsrc(Opc)) 0
596 Result.SRsrc = true; 0
597 if (AMDGPU::getMUBUFHasSoffset(Opc)) 0
598 Result.SOffset = true; 0
599 ----
600 return Result; 0
601 } ----
602 ----
603 if (TII.isMIMG(Opc)) { 0
604 int VAddr0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0); 0
605 if (VAddr0Idx >= 0) { 0
606 int SRsrcIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc); 0
607 Result.NumVAddrs = SRsrcIdx - VAddr0Idx; 0
608 } else { ----
609 Result.VAddr = true; 0
610 } ----
611 Result.SRsrc = true; 0
612 const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(Opc); 0
613 if (Info && AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcodeInfo(Info->BaseOpcode)->Sampler) 0
614 Result.SSamp = true; 0
615 ----
616 return Result; 0
617 } ----
618 if (TII.isMTBUF(Opc)) { 0
619 if (AMDGPU::getMTBUFHasVAddr(Opc)) 0
620 Result.VAddr = true; 0
621 if (AMDGPU::getMTBUFHasSrsrc(Opc)) 0
622 Result.SRsrc = true; 0
623 if (AMDGPU::getMTBUFHasSoffset(Opc)) 0
624 Result.SOffset = true; 0
625 ----
626 return Result; 0
627 } ----
628 ----
629 switch (Opc) { 0
630 default: 0
631 return Result; 0
632 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_SGPR_IMM: 0
633 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_SGPR_IMM: ----
634 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_SGPR_IMM: ----
635 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_SGPR_IMM: ----
636 Result.SOffset = true; 0
637 [[fallthrough]]; ----
638 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: 0
639 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM: ----
640 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
641 case AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
642 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORD_IMM: ----
643 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM: ----
644 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM: ----
645 case AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM: ----
646 Result.SBase = true; 0
647 return Result; 0
648 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32: 0
649 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64: ----
650 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B32_gfx9: ----
651 case AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64_gfx9: ----
652 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B32: ----
653 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64: ----
654 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B32_gfx9: ----
655 case AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64_gfx9: ----
656 Result.Addr = true; 0
657 return Result; 0
658 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORD_SADDR: 0
659 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2_SADDR: ----
660 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3_SADDR: ----
661 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4_SADDR: ----
662 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORD_SADDR: ----
663 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2_SADDR: ----
664 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3_SADDR: ----
665 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4_SADDR: ----
666 Result.SAddr = true; 0
667 [[fallthrough]]; ----
668 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORD: 0
669 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2: ----
670 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3: ----
671 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4: ----
672 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORD: ----
673 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2: ----
674 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3: ----
675 case AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4: ----
676 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORD: ----
677 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX2: ----
678 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX3: ----
679 case AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX4: ----
680 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORD: ----
681 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX2: ----
682 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX3: ----
683 case AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX4: ----
684 Result.VAddr = true; 0
685 return Result; 0
686 } ----
687 } ----
688 ----
689 void SILoadStoreOptimizer::CombineInfo::setMI(MachineBasicBlock::iterator MI, 0
690 const SILoadStoreOptimizer &LSO) { ----
691 I = MI; 0
692 unsigned Opc = MI->getOpcode(); 0
693 InstClass = getInstClass(Opc, *LSO.TII); 0
694 ----
695 if (InstClass == UNKNOWN) 0
696 return; 0
697 ----
698 IsAGPR = LSO.TRI->hasAGPRs(LSO.getDataRegClass(*MI)); 0
699 ----
700 switch (InstClass) { 0
701 case DS_READ: 0
702 EltSize = 0
703 (Opc == AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64 || Opc == AMDGPU::DS_READ_B64_gfx9) ? 8 0
704 : 4; ----
705 break; 0
706 case DS_WRITE: 0
707 EltSize = 0
708 (Opc == AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64 || Opc == AMDGPU::DS_WRITE_B64_gfx9) ? 8 0
709 : 4; ----
710 break; 0
711 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_IMM: 0
712 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM: ----
713 case S_LOAD_IMM: ----
714 EltSize = AMDGPU::convertSMRDOffsetUnits(*LSO.STM, 4); 0
715 break; 0
716 default: 0
717 EltSize = 4; 0
718 break; 0
719 } ----
720 ----
721 if (InstClass == MIMG) { 0
722 DMask = LSO.TII->getNamedOperand(*I, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask)->getImm(); 0
723 // Offset is not considered for MIMG instructions. ----
724 Offset = 0; 0
725 } else { ----
726 int OffsetIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::offset); 0
727 Offset = I->getOperand(OffsetIdx).getImm(); 0
728 } ----
729 ----
730 if (InstClass == TBUFFER_LOAD || InstClass == TBUFFER_STORE) 0
731 Format = LSO.TII->getNamedOperand(*I, AMDGPU::OpName::format)->getImm(); 0
732 ----
733 Width = getOpcodeWidth(*I, *LSO.TII); 0
734 ----
735 if ((InstClass == DS_READ) || (InstClass == DS_WRITE)) { 0
736 Offset &= 0xffff; 0
737 } else if (InstClass != MIMG) { 0
738 CPol = LSO.TII->getNamedOperand(*I, AMDGPU::OpName::cpol)->getImm(); 0
739 } ----
740 ----
741 AddressRegs Regs = getRegs(Opc, *LSO.TII); 0
742 ----
743 NumAddresses = 0; 0
744 for (unsigned J = 0; J < Regs.NumVAddrs; J++) 0
745 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
746 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0) + J; 0
747 if (Regs.Addr) 0
748 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
749 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::addr); 0
750 if (Regs.SBase) 0
751 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
752 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::sbase); 0
753 if (Regs.SRsrc) 0
754 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
755 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc); 0
756 if (Regs.SOffset) 0
757 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
758 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::soffset); 0
759 if (Regs.SAddr) 0
760 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
761 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::saddr); 0
762 if (Regs.VAddr) 0
763 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
764 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr); 0
765 if (Regs.SSamp) 0
766 AddrIdx[NumAddresses++] = 0
767 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::ssamp); 0
768 assert(NumAddresses <= MaxAddressRegs); 0
769 ----
770 for (unsigned J = 0; J < NumAddresses; J++) 0
771 AddrReg[J] = &I->getOperand(AddrIdx[J]); 0
772 } ----
773 ----
774 } // end anonymous namespace. ----

790 static void addDefsUsesToList(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
791 DenseSet &RegDefs, ----
792 DenseSet &RegUses) { ----
793 for (const auto &Op : MI.operands()) { 0
794 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
795 continue; 0
796 if (Op.isDef()) 0
797 RegDefs.insert(Op.getReg()); 0
798 if (Op.readsReg()) 0
799 RegUses.insert(Op.getReg()); 0
800 } ----
801 } 0
802 ----
803 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::canSwapInstructions( 0
804 const DenseSet &ARegDefs, const DenseSet &ARegUses, ----
805 const MachineInstr &A, const MachineInstr &B) const { ----
806 if (A.mayLoadOrStore() && B.mayLoadOrStore() && 0
807 (A.mayStore() || B.mayStore()) && A.mayAlias(AA, B, true)) 0
808 return false; 0
809 for (const auto &BOp : B.operands()) { 0
810 if (!BOp.isReg()) 0
811 continue; 0
812 if ((BOp.isDef() || BOp.readsReg()) && ARegDefs.contains(BOp.getReg())) 0
813 return false; 0
814 if (BOp.isDef() && ARegUses.contains(BOp.getReg())) 0
815 return false; 0
816 } ----
817 return true; 0
818 } ----
819 ----
820 // Given that \p CI and \p Paired are adjacent memory operations produce a new ----
821 // MMO for the combined operation with a new access size. ----
822 MachineMemOperand * ----
823 SILoadStoreOptimizer::combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
824 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
825 const MachineMemOperand *MMOa = *CI.I->memoperands_begin(); 0
826 const MachineMemOperand *MMOb = *Paired.I->memoperands_begin(); 0
827 ----
828 unsigned Size = MMOa->getSize() + MMOb->getSize(); 0
829 ----
830 // A base pointer for the combined operation is the same as the leading ----
831 // operation's pointer. ----
832 if (Paired < CI) 0
833 std::swap(MMOa, MMOb); 0
834 ----
835 MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo(MMOa->getPointerInfo()); 0
836 // If merging FLAT and GLOBAL set address space to FLAT. ----
837 if (MMOb->getAddrSpace() == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) 0
838 PtrInfo.AddrSpace = AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS; 0
839 ----
840 MachineFunction *MF = CI.I->getMF(); 0
841 return MF->getMachineMemOperand(MMOa, PtrInfo, Size); 0
842 } ----
843 ----
844 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::dmasksCanBeCombined(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
845 const SIInstrInfo &TII, ----
846 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
847 assert(CI.InstClass == MIMG); 0
848 ----
849 // Ignore instructions with tfe/lwe set. ----
850 const auto *TFEOp = TII.getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe); 0
851 const auto *LWEOp = TII.getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::lwe); 0
852 ----
853 if ((TFEOp && TFEOp->getImm()) || (LWEOp && LWEOp->getImm())) 0
854 return false; 0
855 ----
856 // Check other optional immediate operands for equality. ----
857 unsigned OperandsToMatch[] = {AMDGPU::OpName::cpol, AMDGPU::OpName::d16, 0
858 AMDGPU::OpName::unorm, AMDGPU::OpName::da, ----
859 AMDGPU::OpName::r128, AMDGPU::OpName::a16}; ----
860 ----
861 for (auto op : OperandsToMatch) { 0
862 int Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(CI.I->getOpcode(), op); 0
863 if (AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Paired.I->getOpcode(), op) != Idx) 0
864 return false; 0
865 if (Idx != -1 && 0
866 CI.I->getOperand(Idx).getImm() != Paired.I->getOperand(Idx).getImm()) 0
867 return false; 0
868 } ----
869 ----
870 // Check DMask for overlaps. ----
871 unsigned MaxMask = std::max(CI.DMask, Paired.DMask); 0
872 unsigned MinMask = std::min(CI.DMask, Paired.DMask); 0
873 ----
874 unsigned AllowedBitsForMin = llvm::countr_zero(MaxMask); 0
875 if ((1u << AllowedBitsForMin) <= MinMask) 0
876 return false; 0
877 ----
878 return true; 0
879 } ----
880 ----
881 static unsigned getBufferFormatWithCompCount(unsigned OldFormat, 0
882 unsigned ComponentCount, ----
883 const GCNSubtarget &STI) { ----
884 if (ComponentCount > 4) 0
885 return 0; 0
886 ----
887 const llvm::AMDGPU::GcnBufferFormatInfo *OldFormatInfo = ----
888 llvm::AMDGPU::getGcnBufferFormatInfo(OldFormat, STI); 0
889 if (!OldFormatInfo) 0
890 return 0; 0
891 ----
892 const llvm::AMDGPU::GcnBufferFormatInfo *NewFormatInfo = ----
893 llvm::AMDGPU::getGcnBufferFormatInfo(OldFormatInfo->BitsPerComp, 0
894 ComponentCount, ----
895 OldFormatInfo->NumFormat, STI); 0
896 ----
897 if (!NewFormatInfo) 0
898 return 0; 0
899 ----
900 assert(NewFormatInfo->NumFormat == OldFormatInfo->NumFormat && 0
901 NewFormatInfo->BitsPerComp == OldFormatInfo->BitsPerComp); ----
902 ----
903 return NewFormatInfo->Format; 0
904 } ----
905 ----
906 // Return the value in the inclusive range [Lo,Hi] that is aligned to the ----
907 // highest power of two. Note that the result is well defined for all inputs ----
908 // including corner cases like: ----
909 // - if Lo == Hi, return that value ----
910 // - if Lo == 0, return 0 (even though the "- 1" below underflows ----
911 // - if Lo > Hi, return 0 (as if the range wrapped around) ----
912 static uint32_t mostAlignedValueInRange(uint32_t Lo, uint32_t Hi) { 0
913 return Hi & maskLeadingOnes(llvm::countl_zero((Lo - 1) ^ Hi) + 1); 0
914 } ----
915 ----
916 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::offsetsCanBeCombined(CombineInfo &CI, 0
917 const GCNSubtarget &STI, ----
918 CombineInfo &Paired, ----
919 bool Modify) { ----
920 assert(CI.InstClass != MIMG); 0
921 ----
922 // XXX - Would the same offset be OK? Is there any reason this would happen or ----
923 // be useful? ----
924 if (CI.Offset == Paired.Offset) 0
925 return false; 0
926 ----
927 // This won't be valid if the offset isn't aligned. ----
928 if ((CI.Offset % CI.EltSize != 0) || (Paired.Offset % CI.EltSize != 0)) 0
929 return false; 0
930 ----
931 if (CI.InstClass == TBUFFER_LOAD || CI.InstClass == TBUFFER_STORE) { 0
932 ----
933 const llvm::AMDGPU::GcnBufferFormatInfo *Info0 = ----
934 llvm::AMDGPU::getGcnBufferFormatInfo(CI.Format, STI); 0
935 if (!Info0) 0
936 return false; 0
937 const llvm::AMDGPU::GcnBufferFormatInfo *Info1 = ----
938 llvm::AMDGPU::getGcnBufferFormatInfo(Paired.Format, STI); 0
939 if (!Info1) 0
940 return false; 0
941 ----
942 if (Info0->BitsPerComp != Info1->BitsPerComp || 0
943 Info0->NumFormat != Info1->NumFormat) 0
944 return false; 0
945 ----
946 // TODO: Should be possible to support more formats, but if format loads ----
947 // are not dword-aligned, the merged load might not be valid. ----
948 if (Info0->BitsPerComp != 32) 0
949 return false; 0
950 ----
951 if (getBufferFormatWithCompCount(CI.Format, CI.Width + Paired.Width, STI) == 0) 0
952 return false; 0
953 } ----
954 ----
955 uint32_t EltOffset0 = CI.Offset / CI.EltSize; 0
956 uint32_t EltOffset1 = Paired.Offset / CI.EltSize; 0
957 CI.UseST64 = false; 0
958 CI.BaseOff = 0; 0
959 ----
960 // Handle all non-DS instructions. ----
961 if ((CI.InstClass != DS_READ) && (CI.InstClass != DS_WRITE)) { 0
962 if (EltOffset0 + CI.Width != EltOffset1 && 0
963 EltOffset1 + Paired.Width != EltOffset0) 0
964 return false; 0
965 if (CI.CPol != Paired.CPol) 0
966 return false; 0
967 return true; 0
968 } ----
969 ----
970 // If the offset in elements doesn't fit in 8-bits, we might be able to use ----
971 // the stride 64 versions. ----
972 if ((EltOffset0 % 64 == 0) && (EltOffset1 % 64) == 0 && 0
973 isUInt<8>(EltOffset0 / 64) && isUInt<8>(EltOffset1 / 64)) { 0
974 if (Modify) { 0
975 CI.Offset = EltOffset0 / 64; 0
976 Paired.Offset = EltOffset1 / 64; 0
977 CI.UseST64 = true; 0
978 } ----
979 return true; 0
980 } ----
981 ----
982 // Check if the new offsets fit in the reduced 8-bit range. ----
983 if (isUInt<8>(EltOffset0) && isUInt<8>(EltOffset1)) { 0
984 if (Modify) { 0
985 CI.Offset = EltOffset0; 0
986 Paired.Offset = EltOffset1; 0
987 } ----
988 return true; 0
989 } ----
990 ----
991 // Try to shift base address to decrease offsets. ----
992 uint32_t Min = std::min(EltOffset0, EltOffset1); 0
993 uint32_t Max = std::max(EltOffset0, EltOffset1); 0
994 ----
995 const uint32_t Mask = maskTrailingOnes(8) * 64; 0
996 if (((Max - Min) & ~Mask) == 0) { 0
997 if (Modify) { 0
998 // From the range of values we could use for BaseOff, choose the one that ----
999 // is aligned to the highest power of two, to maximise the chance that ----
1000 // the same offset can be reused for other load/store pairs. ----
1001 uint32_t BaseOff = mostAlignedValueInRange(Max - 0xff * 64, Min); 0
1002 // Copy the low bits of the offsets, so that when we adjust them by ----
1003 // subtracting BaseOff they will be multiples of 64. ----
1004 BaseOff |= Min & maskTrailingOnes(6); 0
1005 CI.BaseOff = BaseOff * CI.EltSize; 0
1006 CI.Offset = (EltOffset0 - BaseOff) / 64; 0
1007 Paired.Offset = (EltOffset1 - BaseOff) / 64; 0
1008 CI.UseST64 = true; 0
1009 } ----
1010 return true; 0
1011 } ----
1012 ----
1013 if (isUInt<8>(Max - Min)) { 0
1014 if (Modify) { 0
1015 // From the range of values we could use for BaseOff, choose the one that ----
1016 // is aligned to the highest power of two, to maximise the chance that ----
1017 // the same offset can be reused for other load/store pairs. ----
1018 uint32_t BaseOff = mostAlignedValueInRange(Max - 0xff, Min); 0
1019 CI.BaseOff = BaseOff * CI.EltSize; 0
1020 CI.Offset = EltOffset0 - BaseOff; 0
1021 Paired.Offset = EltOffset1 - BaseOff; 0
1022 } ----
1023 return true; 0
1024 } ----
1025 ----
1026 return false; 0
1027 } ----
1028 ----
1029 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::widthsFit(const GCNSubtarget &STM, 0
1030 const CombineInfo &CI, ----
1031 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
1032 const unsigned Width = (CI.Width + Paired.Width); 0
1033 switch (CI.InstClass) { 0
1034 default: 0
1035 return (Width <= 4) && (STM.hasDwordx3LoadStores() || (Width != 3)); 0
1036 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_IMM: 0
1037 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM: ----
1038 case S_LOAD_IMM: ----
1039 switch (Width) { 0
1040 default: 0
1041 return false; 0
1042 case 2: 0
1043 case 4: ----
1044 case 8: ----
1045 return true; 0
1046 } ----
1047 } ----
1048 } ----
1049 ----
1050 const TargetRegisterClass * ----
1051 SILoadStoreOptimizer::getDataRegClass(const MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1052 if (const auto *Dst = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst)) { 0
1053 return TRI->getRegClassForReg(*MRI, Dst->getReg()); 0
1054 } ----
1055 if (const auto *Src = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata)) { 0
1056 return TRI->getRegClassForReg(*MRI, Src->getReg()); 0
1057 } ----
1058 if (const auto *Src = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::data0)) { 0
1059 return TRI->getRegClassForReg(*MRI, Src->getReg()); 0
1060 } ----
1061 if (const auto *Dst = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst)) { 0
1062 return TRI->getRegClassForReg(*MRI, Dst->getReg()); 0
1063 } ----
1064 if (const auto *Src = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::sdata)) { 0
1065 return TRI->getRegClassForReg(*MRI, Src->getReg()); 0
1066 } ----
1067 return nullptr; 0
1068 } ----
1069 ----
1070 /// This function assumes that CI comes before Paired in a basic block. Return ----
1071 /// an insertion point for the merged instruction or nullptr on failure. ----
1072 SILoadStoreOptimizer::CombineInfo * ----
1073 SILoadStoreOptimizer::checkAndPrepareMerge(CombineInfo &CI, 0
1074 CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
1075 // If another instruction has already been merged into CI, it may now be a ----
1076 // type that we can't do any further merging into. ----
1077 if (CI.InstClass == UNKNOWN || Paired.InstClass == UNKNOWN) 0
1078 return nullptr; 0
1079 assert(CI.InstClass == Paired.InstClass); 0
1080 ----
1081 if (getInstSubclass(CI.I->getOpcode(), *TII) != 0
1082 getInstSubclass(Paired.I->getOpcode(), *TII)) 0
1083 return nullptr; 0
1084 ----
1085 // Check both offsets (or masks for MIMG) can be combined and fit in the ----
1086 // reduced range. ----
1087 if (CI.InstClass == MIMG) { 0
1088 if (!dmasksCanBeCombined(CI, *TII, Paired)) 0
1089 return nullptr; 0
1090 } else { ----
1091 if (!widthsFit(*STM, CI, Paired) || !offsetsCanBeCombined(CI, *STM, Paired)) 0
1092 return nullptr; 0
1093 } ----
1094 ----
1095 DenseSet RegDefs; 0
1096 DenseSet RegUses; 0
1097 CombineInfo *Where; ----
1098 if (CI.I->mayLoad()) { 0
1099 // Try to hoist Paired up to CI. ----
1100 addDefsUsesToList(*Paired.I, RegDefs, RegUses); 0
1101 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = Paired.I; --MBBI != CI.I;) { 0
1102 if (!canSwapInstructions(RegDefs, RegUses, *Paired.I, *MBBI)) 0
1103 return nullptr; 0
1104 } ----
1105 Where = &CI; 0
1106 } else { ----
1107 // Try to sink CI down to Paired. ----
1108 addDefsUsesToList(*CI.I, RegDefs, RegUses); 0
1109 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = CI.I; ++MBBI != Paired.I;) { 0
1110 if (!canSwapInstructions(RegDefs, RegUses, *CI.I, *MBBI)) 0
1111 return nullptr; 0
1112 } ----
1113 Where = &Paired; 0
1114 } ----
1115 ----
1116 // Call offsetsCanBeCombined with modify = true so that the offsets are ----
1117 // correct for the new instruction. This should return true, because ----
1118 // this function should only be called on CombineInfo objects that ----
1119 // have already been confirmed to be mergeable. ----
1120 if (CI.InstClass == DS_READ || CI.InstClass == DS_WRITE) 0
1121 offsetsCanBeCombined(CI, *STM, Paired, true); 0
1122 return Where; 0
1123 } 0
1124 ----
1125 unsigned SILoadStoreOptimizer::read2Opcode(unsigned EltSize) const { 0
1126 if (STM->ldsRequiresM0Init()) 0
1127 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_READ2_B32 : AMDGPU::DS_READ2_B64; 0
1128 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_READ2_B32_gfx9 : AMDGPU::DS_READ2_B64_gfx9; 0
1129 } ----
1130 ----
1131 unsigned SILoadStoreOptimizer::read2ST64Opcode(unsigned EltSize) const { 0
1132 if (STM->ldsRequiresM0Init()) 0
1133 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_READ2ST64_B32 : AMDGPU::DS_READ2ST64_B64; 0
1134 ----
1135 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_READ2ST64_B32_gfx9 0
1136 : AMDGPU::DS_READ2ST64_B64_gfx9; 0
1137 } ----
1138 ----
1139 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1140 SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeRead2Pair(CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, 0
1141 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1142 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1143 ----
1144 // Be careful, since the addresses could be subregisters themselves in weird ----
1145 // cases, like vectors of pointers. ----
1146 const auto *AddrReg = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::addr); 0
1147 ----
1148 const auto *Dest0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1149 const auto *Dest1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1150 ----
1151 unsigned NewOffset0 = CI.Offset; 0
1152 unsigned NewOffset1 = Paired.Offset; 0
1153 unsigned Opc = ----
1154 CI.UseST64 ? read2ST64Opcode(CI.EltSize) : read2Opcode(CI.EltSize); 0
1155 ----
1156 unsigned SubRegIdx0 = (CI.EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::sub0 : AMDGPU::sub0_sub1; 0
1157 unsigned SubRegIdx1 = (CI.EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::sub1 : AMDGPU::sub2_sub3; 0
1158 ----
1159 if (NewOffset0 > NewOffset1) { 0
1160 // Canonicalize the merged instruction so the smaller offset comes first. ----
1161 std::swap(NewOffset0, NewOffset1); 0
1162 std::swap(SubRegIdx0, SubRegIdx1); 0
1163 } ----
1164 ----
1165 assert((isUInt<8>(NewOffset0) && isUInt<8>(NewOffset1)) && 0
1166 (NewOffset0 != NewOffset1) && "Computed offset doesn't fit"); ----
1167 ----
1168 const MCInstrDesc &Read2Desc = TII->get(Opc); 0
1169 ----
1170 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1171 Register DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1172 ----
1173 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1174 ----
1175 Register BaseReg = AddrReg->getReg(); 0
1176 unsigned BaseSubReg = AddrReg->getSubReg(); 0
1177 unsigned BaseRegFlags = 0; 0
1178 if (CI.BaseOff) { 0
1179 Register ImmReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass); 0
1180 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), ImmReg) 0
1181 .addImm(CI.BaseOff); 0
1182 ----
1183 BaseReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass); 0
1184 BaseRegFlags = RegState::Kill; 0
1185 ----
1186 TII->getAddNoCarry(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, BaseReg) 0
1187 .addReg(ImmReg) 0
1188 .addReg(AddrReg->getReg(), 0, BaseSubReg) 0
1189 .addImm(0); // clamp bit 0
1190 BaseSubReg = 0; 0
1191 } ----
1192 ----
1193 MachineInstrBuilder Read2 = ----
1194 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, Read2Desc, DestReg) 0
1195 .addReg(BaseReg, BaseRegFlags, BaseSubReg) // addr 0
1196 .addImm(NewOffset0) // offset0 0
1197 .addImm(NewOffset1) // offset1 0
1198 .addImm(0) // gds 0
1199 .cloneMergedMemRefs({&*CI.I, &*Paired.I}); 0
1200 ----
1201 (void)Read2; ----
1202 ----
1203 const MCInstrDesc &CopyDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
1204 ----
1205 // Copy to the old destination registers. ----
1206 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1207 .add(*Dest0) // Copy to same destination including flags and sub reg. 0
1208 .addReg(DestReg, 0, SubRegIdx0); 0
1209 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1210 .add(*Dest1) 0
1211 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Kill, SubRegIdx1); 0
1212 ----
1213 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1214 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1215 ----
1216 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Inserted read2: " << *Read2 << '\n'); 0
1217 return Read2; 0
1218 } 0
1219 ----
1220 unsigned SILoadStoreOptimizer::write2Opcode(unsigned EltSize) const { 0
1221 if (STM->ldsRequiresM0Init()) 0
1222 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2_B32 : AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2_B64; 0
1223 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2_B32_gfx9 0
1224 : AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2_B64_gfx9; 0
1225 } ----
1226 ----
1227 unsigned SILoadStoreOptimizer::write2ST64Opcode(unsigned EltSize) const { 0
1228 if (STM->ldsRequiresM0Init()) 0
1229 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2ST64_B32 0
1230 : AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2ST64_B64; 0
1231 ----
1232 return (EltSize == 4) ? AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2ST64_B32_gfx9 0
1233 : AMDGPU::DS_WRITE2ST64_B64_gfx9; 0
1234 } ----
1235 ----
1236 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeWrite2Pair( 0
1237 CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, ----
1238 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1239 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1240 ----
1241 // Be sure to use .addOperand(), and not .addReg() with these. We want to be ----
1242 // sure we preserve the subregister index and any register flags set on them. ----
1243 const MachineOperand *AddrReg = ----
1244 TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::addr); 0
1245 const MachineOperand *Data0 = ----
1246 TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::data0); 0
1247 const MachineOperand *Data1 = ----
1248 TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::data0); 0
1249 ----
1250 unsigned NewOffset0 = CI.Offset; 0
1251 unsigned NewOffset1 = Paired.Offset; 0
1252 unsigned Opc = ----
1253 CI.UseST64 ? write2ST64Opcode(CI.EltSize) : write2Opcode(CI.EltSize); 0
1254 ----
1255 if (NewOffset0 > NewOffset1) { 0
1256 // Canonicalize the merged instruction so the smaller offset comes first. ----
1257 std::swap(NewOffset0, NewOffset1); 0
1258 std::swap(Data0, Data1); 0
1259 } ----
1260 ----
1261 assert((isUInt<8>(NewOffset0) && isUInt<8>(NewOffset1)) && 0
1262 (NewOffset0 != NewOffset1) && "Computed offset doesn't fit"); ----
1263 ----
1264 const MCInstrDesc &Write2Desc = TII->get(Opc); 0
1265 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1266 ----
1267 Register BaseReg = AddrReg->getReg(); 0
1268 unsigned BaseSubReg = AddrReg->getSubReg(); 0
1269 unsigned BaseRegFlags = 0; 0
1270 if (CI.BaseOff) { 0
1271 Register ImmReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass); 0
1272 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), ImmReg) 0
1273 .addImm(CI.BaseOff); 0
1274 ----
1275 BaseReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass); 0
1276 BaseRegFlags = RegState::Kill; 0
1277 ----
1278 TII->getAddNoCarry(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, BaseReg) 0
1279 .addReg(ImmReg) 0
1280 .addReg(AddrReg->getReg(), 0, BaseSubReg) 0
1281 .addImm(0); // clamp bit 0
1282 BaseSubReg = 0; 0
1283 } ----
1284 ----
1285 MachineInstrBuilder Write2 = ----
1286 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, Write2Desc) 0
1287 .addReg(BaseReg, BaseRegFlags, BaseSubReg) // addr 0
1288 .add(*Data0) // data0 0
1289 .add(*Data1) // data1 0
1290 .addImm(NewOffset0) // offset0 0
1291 .addImm(NewOffset1) // offset1 0
1292 .addImm(0) // gds 0
1293 .cloneMergedMemRefs({&*CI.I, &*Paired.I}); 0
1294 ----
1295 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1296 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1297 ----
1298 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Inserted write2 inst: " << *Write2 << '\n'); 0
1299 return Write2; 0
1300 } 0
1301 ----
1302 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
1303 SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeImagePair(CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, 0
1304 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1305 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1306 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1307 const unsigned Opcode = getNewOpcode(CI, Paired); 0
1308 ----
1309 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1310 ----
1311 Register DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1312 unsigned MergedDMask = CI.DMask | Paired.DMask; 0
1313 unsigned DMaskIdx = ----
1314 AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(CI.I->getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::dmask); 0
1315 ----
1316 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode), DestReg); 0
1317 for (unsigned I = 1, E = (*CI.I).getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) { 0
1318 if (I == DMaskIdx) 0
1319 MIB.addImm(MergedDMask); 0
1320 else ----
1321 MIB.add((*CI.I).getOperand(I)); 0
1322 } ----
1323 ----
1324 // It shouldn't be possible to get this far if the two instructions ----
1325 // don't have a single memoperand, because MachineInstr::mayAlias() ----
1326 // will return true if this is the case. ----
1327 assert(CI.I->hasOneMemOperand() && Paired.I->hasOneMemOperand()); 0
1328 ----
1329 MachineInstr *New = MIB.addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1330 ----
1331 unsigned SubRegIdx0, SubRegIdx1; ----
1332 std::tie(SubRegIdx0, SubRegIdx1) = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1333 ----
1334 // Copy to the old destination registers. ----
1335 const MCInstrDesc &CopyDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
1336 const auto *Dest0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1337 const auto *Dest1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1338 ----
1339 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1340 .add(*Dest0) // Copy to same destination including flags and sub reg. 0
1341 .addReg(DestReg, 0, SubRegIdx0); 0
1342 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1343 .add(*Dest1) 0
1344 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Kill, SubRegIdx1); 0
1345 ----
1346 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1347 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1348 return New; 0
1349 } 0
1350 ----
1351 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeSMemLoadImmPair( 0
1352 CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, ----
1353 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1354 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1355 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1356 const unsigned Opcode = getNewOpcode(CI, Paired); 0
1357 ----
1358 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1359 ----
1360 Register DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1361 unsigned MergedOffset = std::min(CI.Offset, Paired.Offset); 0
1362 ----
1363 // It shouldn't be possible to get this far if the two instructions ----
1364 // don't have a single memoperand, because MachineInstr::mayAlias() ----
1365 // will return true if this is the case. ----
1366 assert(CI.I->hasOneMemOperand() && Paired.I->hasOneMemOperand()); 0
1367 ----
1368 MachineInstrBuilder New = ----
1369 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode), DestReg) 0
1370 .add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::sbase)); 0
1371 if (CI.InstClass == S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM) 0
1372 New.add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::soffset)); 0
1373 New.addImm(MergedOffset); 0
1374 New.addImm(CI.CPol).addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1375 ----
1376 std::pair SubRegIdx = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1377 const unsigned SubRegIdx0 = std::get<0>(SubRegIdx); 0
1378 const unsigned SubRegIdx1 = std::get<1>(SubRegIdx); 0
1379 ----
1380 // Copy to the old destination registers. ----
1381 const MCInstrDesc &CopyDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
1382 const auto *Dest0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst); 0
1383 const auto *Dest1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst); 0
1384 ----
1385 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1386 .add(*Dest0) // Copy to same destination including flags and sub reg. 0
1387 .addReg(DestReg, 0, SubRegIdx0); 0
1388 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1389 .add(*Dest1) 0
1390 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Kill, SubRegIdx1); 0
1391 ----
1392 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1393 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1394 return New; 0
1395 } 0

1397 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeBufferLoadPair( 0

1408 Register DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0

1427 .addImm(CI.CPol) // cpol 0
1428 .addImm(0) // swz 0
1429 .addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1430 ----
1431 std::pair SubRegIdx = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1432 const unsigned SubRegIdx0 = std::get<0>(SubRegIdx); 0
1433 const unsigned SubRegIdx1 = std::get<1>(SubRegIdx); 0
1434 ----
1435 // Copy to the old destination registers. ----
1436 const MCInstrDesc &CopyDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
1437 const auto *Dest0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1438 const auto *Dest1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1439 ----
1440 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1441 .add(*Dest0) // Copy to same destination including flags and sub reg. 0
1442 .addReg(DestReg, 0, SubRegIdx0); 0
1443 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1444 .add(*Dest1) 0
1445 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Kill, SubRegIdx1); 0

1566 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeFlatLoadPair( 0
1567 CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, ----
1568 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1569 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1570 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1571 ----
1572 const unsigned Opcode = getNewOpcode(CI, Paired); 0
1573 ----
1574 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1575 Register DestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1576 ----
1577 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode), DestReg); 0
1578 ----
1579 if (auto *SAddr = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::saddr)) 0
1580 MIB.add(*SAddr); 0
1581 ----
1582 MachineInstr *New = ----
1583 MIB.add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr)) 0
1584 .addImm(std::min(CI.Offset, Paired.Offset)) 0
1585 .addImm(CI.CPol) 0
1586 .addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1587 ----
1588 std::pair SubRegIdx = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1589 const unsigned SubRegIdx0 = std::get<0>(SubRegIdx); 0
1590 const unsigned SubRegIdx1 = std::get<1>(SubRegIdx); 0
1591 ----
1592 // Copy to the old destination registers. ----
1593 const MCInstrDesc &CopyDesc = TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY); 0
1594 const auto *Dest0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1595 const auto *Dest1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst); 0
1596 ----
1597 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1598 .add(*Dest0) // Copy to same destination including flags and sub reg. 0
1599 .addReg(DestReg, 0, SubRegIdx0); 0
1600 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, CopyDesc) 0
1601 .add(*Dest1) 0
1602 .addReg(DestReg, RegState::Kill, SubRegIdx1); 0
1603 ----
1604 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1605 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1606 return New; 0
1607 } 0
1608 ----
1609 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeFlatStorePair( 0
1610 CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, ----
1611 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1612 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1613 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1614 ----
1615 const unsigned Opcode = getNewOpcode(CI, Paired); 0
1616 ----
1617 std::pair SubRegIdx = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1618 const unsigned SubRegIdx0 = std::get<0>(SubRegIdx); 0
1619 const unsigned SubRegIdx1 = std::get<1>(SubRegIdx); 0
1620 ----
1621 // Copy to the new source register. ----
1622 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1623 Register SrcReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1624 ----
1625 const auto *Src0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1626 const auto *Src1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1627 ----
1628 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), SrcReg) 0
1629 .add(*Src0) 0
1630 .addImm(SubRegIdx0) 0
1631 .add(*Src1) 0
1632 .addImm(SubRegIdx1); 0
1633 ----
1634 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode)) 0
1635 .add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr)) 0
1636 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1637 ----
1638 if (auto *SAddr = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::saddr)) 0
1639 MIB.add(*SAddr); 0
1640 ----
1641 MachineInstr *New = ----
1642 MIB.addImm(std::min(CI.Offset, Paired.Offset)) 0
1643 .addImm(CI.CPol) 0
1644 .addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1645 ----
1646 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1647 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1648 return New; 0
1649 } 0
1650 ----
1651 unsigned SILoadStoreOptimizer::getNewOpcode(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
1652 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
1653 const unsigned Width = CI.Width + Paired.Width; 0
1654 ----
1655 switch (getCommonInstClass(CI, Paired)) { 0
1656 default: 0
1657 assert(CI.InstClass == BUFFER_LOAD || CI.InstClass == BUFFER_STORE); 0
1658 // FIXME: Handle d16 correctly ----
1659 return AMDGPU::getMUBUFOpcode(AMDGPU::getMUBUFBaseOpcode(CI.I->getOpcode()), 0
1660 Width); 0
1661 case TBUFFER_LOAD: 0
1662 case TBUFFER_STORE: ----
1663 return AMDGPU::getMTBUFOpcode(AMDGPU::getMTBUFBaseOpcode(CI.I->getOpcode()), 0
1664 Width); 0
1665 ----
1666 case UNKNOWN: 0
1667 llvm_unreachable("Unknown instruction class"); 0
1668 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_IMM: 0
1669 switch (Width) { 0
1670 default: 0
1671 return 0; 0
1672 case 2: 0
1673 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM; 0
1674 case 4: 0
1675 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM; 0
1676 case 8: 0
1677 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM; 0
1678 } ----
1679 case S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM: 0
1680 switch (Width) { 0
1681 default: 0
1682 return 0; 0
1683 case 2: 0
1684 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX2_SGPR_IMM; 0
1685 case 4: 0
1686 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX4_SGPR_IMM; 0
1687 case 8: 0
1688 return AMDGPU::S_BUFFER_LOAD_DWORDX8_SGPR_IMM; 0
1689 } ----
1690 case S_LOAD_IMM: 0
1691 switch (Width) { 0
1692 default: 0
1693 return 0; 0
1694 case 2: 0
1695 return AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX2_IMM; 0
1696 case 4: 0
1697 return AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX4_IMM; 0
1698 case 8: 0
1699 return AMDGPU::S_LOAD_DWORDX8_IMM; 0
1700 } ----
1701 case GLOBAL_LOAD: 0
1702 switch (Width) { 0
1703 default: 0
1704 return 0; 0
1705 case 2: 0
1706 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2; 0
1707 case 3: 0
1708 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3; 0
1709 case 4: 0
1710 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4; 0
1711 } ----
1712 case GLOBAL_LOAD_SADDR: 0
1713 switch (Width) { 0
1714 default: 0
1715 return 0; 0
1716 case 2: 0
1717 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX2_SADDR; 0
1718 case 3: 0
1719 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX3_SADDR; 0
1720 case 4: 0
1721 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_DWORDX4_SADDR; 0
1722 } ----
1723 case GLOBAL_STORE: 0
1724 switch (Width) { 0
1725 default: 0
1726 return 0; 0
1727 case 2: 0
1728 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2; 0
1729 case 3: 0
1730 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3; 0
1731 case 4: 0
1732 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4; 0
1733 } ----
1734 case GLOBAL_STORE_SADDR: 0
1735 switch (Width) { 0
1736 default: 0
1737 return 0; 0
1738 case 2: 0
1739 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX2_SADDR; 0
1740 case 3: 0
1741 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX3_SADDR; 0
1742 case 4: 0
1743 return AMDGPU::GLOBAL_STORE_DWORDX4_SADDR; 0
1744 } ----
1745 case FLAT_LOAD: 0
1746 switch (Width) { 0
1747 default: 0
1748 return 0; 0
1749 case 2: 0
1750 return AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX2; 0
1751 case 3: 0
1752 return AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX3; 0
1753 case 4: 0
1754 return AMDGPU::FLAT_LOAD_DWORDX4; 0
1755 } ----
1756 case FLAT_STORE: 0
1757 switch (Width) { 0
1758 default: 0
1759 return 0; 0
1760 case 2: 0
1761 return AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX2; 0
1762 case 3: 0
1763 return AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX3; 0
1764 case 4: 0
1765 return AMDGPU::FLAT_STORE_DWORDX4; 0
1766 } ----
1767 case MIMG: 0
1768 assert(((unsigned)llvm::popcount(CI.DMask | Paired.DMask) == Width) && 0
1769 "No overlaps"); ----
1770 return AMDGPU::getMaskedMIMGOp(CI.I->getOpcode(), Width); 0
1771 } ----
1772 } ----
1773 ----
1774 std::pair ----
1775 SILoadStoreOptimizer::getSubRegIdxs(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
1776 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
1777 assert((CI.InstClass != MIMG || 0
1778 ((unsigned)llvm::popcount(CI.DMask | Paired.DMask) == ----
1779 CI.Width + Paired.Width)) && ----
1780 "No overlaps"); ----
1781 ----
1782 unsigned Idx0; ----
1783 unsigned Idx1; ----
1784 ----
1785 static const unsigned Idxs[5][4] = { ----
1786 {AMDGPU::sub0, AMDGPU::sub0_sub1, AMDGPU::sub0_sub1_sub2, AMDGPU::sub0_sub1_sub2_sub3}, ----
1787 {AMDGPU::sub1, AMDGPU::sub1_sub2, AMDGPU::sub1_sub2_sub3, AMDGPU::sub1_sub2_sub3_sub4}, ----
1788 {AMDGPU::sub2, AMDGPU::sub2_sub3, AMDGPU::sub2_sub3_sub4, AMDGPU::sub2_sub3_sub4_sub5}, ----
1789 {AMDGPU::sub3, AMDGPU::sub3_sub4, AMDGPU::sub3_sub4_sub5, AMDGPU::sub3_sub4_sub5_sub6}, ----
1790 {AMDGPU::sub4, AMDGPU::sub4_sub5, AMDGPU::sub4_sub5_sub6, AMDGPU::sub4_sub5_sub6_sub7}, ----
1791 }; ----
1792 ----
1793 assert(CI.Width >= 1 && CI.Width <= 4); 0
1794 assert(Paired.Width >= 1 && Paired.Width <= 4); 0
1795 ----
1796 if (Paired < CI) { 0
1797 Idx1 = Idxs[0][Paired.Width - 1]; 0
1798 Idx0 = Idxs[Paired.Width][CI.Width - 1]; 0
1799 } else { ----
1800 Idx0 = Idxs[0][CI.Width - 1]; 0
1801 Idx1 = Idxs[CI.Width][Paired.Width - 1]; 0
1802 } ----
1803 ----
1804 return std::pair(Idx0, Idx1); 0
1805 } ----
1806 ----
1807 const TargetRegisterClass * ----
1808 SILoadStoreOptimizer::getTargetRegisterClass(const CombineInfo &CI, 0
1809 const CombineInfo &Paired) { ----
1810 if (CI.InstClass == S_BUFFER_LOAD_IMM || 0
1811 CI.InstClass == S_BUFFER_LOAD_SGPR_IMM || CI.InstClass == S_LOAD_IMM) { 0
1812 switch (CI.Width + Paired.Width) { 0
1813 default: 0
1814 return nullptr; 0
1815 case 2: 0
1816 return &AMDGPU::SReg_64_XEXECRegClass; 0
1817 case 4: 0
1818 return &AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClass; 0
1819 case 8: 0
1820 return &AMDGPU::SGPR_256RegClass; 0
1821 case 16: 0
1822 return &AMDGPU::SGPR_512RegClass; 0
1823 } ----
1824 } ----
1825 ----
1826 unsigned BitWidth = 32 * (CI.Width + Paired.Width); 0
1827 return TRI->isAGPRClass(getDataRegClass(*CI.I)) 0
1828 ? TRI->getAGPRClassForBitWidth(BitWidth) 0
1829 : TRI->getVGPRClassForBitWidth(BitWidth); 0
1830 } ----
1831 ----
1832 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SILoadStoreOptimizer::mergeBufferStorePair( 0
1833 CombineInfo &CI, CombineInfo &Paired, ----
1834 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore) { ----
1835 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = CI.I->getParent(); 0
1836 DebugLoc DL = CI.I->getDebugLoc(); 0
1837 ----
1838 const unsigned Opcode = getNewOpcode(CI, Paired); 0
1839 ----
1840 std::pair SubRegIdx = getSubRegIdxs(CI, Paired); 0
1841 const unsigned SubRegIdx0 = std::get<0>(SubRegIdx); 0
1842 const unsigned SubRegIdx1 = std::get<1>(SubRegIdx); 0
1843 ----
1844 // Copy to the new source register. ----
1845 const TargetRegisterClass *SuperRC = getTargetRegisterClass(CI, Paired); 0
1846 Register SrcReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(SuperRC); 0
1847 ----
1848 const auto *Src0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1849 const auto *Src1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*Paired.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata); 0
1850 ----
1851 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE), SrcReg) 0
1852 .add(*Src0) 0
1853 .addImm(SubRegIdx0) 0
1854 .add(*Src1) 0
1855 .addImm(SubRegIdx1); 0
1856 ----
1857 auto MIB = BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, DL, TII->get(Opcode)) 0
1858 .addReg(SrcReg, RegState::Kill); 0
1859 ----
1860 AddressRegs Regs = getRegs(Opcode, *TII); 0
1861 ----
1862 if (Regs.VAddr) 0
1863 MIB.add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr)); 0
1864 ----
1865 ----
1866 // It shouldn't be possible to get this far if the two instructions ----
1867 // don't have a single memoperand, because MachineInstr::mayAlias() ----
1868 // will return true if this is the case. ----
1869 assert(CI.I->hasOneMemOperand() && Paired.I->hasOneMemOperand()); 0
1870 ----
1871 MachineInstr *New = ----
1872 MIB.add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc)) 0
1873 .add(*TII->getNamedOperand(*CI.I, AMDGPU::OpName::soffset)) 0
1874 .addImm(std::min(CI.Offset, Paired.Offset)) // offset 0
1875 .addImm(CI.CPol) // cpol 0
1876 .addImm(0) // swz 0
1877 .addMemOperand(combineKnownAdjacentMMOs(CI, Paired)); 0
1878 ----
1879 CI.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1880 Paired.I->eraseFromParent(); 0
1881 return New; 0
1882 } 0
1883 ----
1884 MachineOperand ----
1885 SILoadStoreOptimizer::createRegOrImm(int32_t Val, MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1886 APInt V(32, Val, true); 0
1887 if (TII->isInlineConstant(V)) 0
1888 return MachineOperand::CreateImm(Val); 0
1889 ----
1890 Register Reg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass); 0
1891 MachineInstr *Mov = ----
1892 BuildMI(*MI.getParent(), MI.getIterator(), MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
1893 TII->get(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32), Reg) 0
1894 .addImm(Val); 0
1895 (void)Mov; ----
1896 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "; Mov->dump()); 0
1897 return MachineOperand::CreateReg(Reg, false); 0
1898 } 0
1899 ----
1900 // Compute base address using Addr and return the final register. ----
1901 Register SILoadStoreOptimizer::computeBase(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1902 const MemAddress &Addr) const { ----
1903 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
1904 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MI.getIterator(); 0
1905 DebugLoc DL = MI.getDebugLoc(); 0
1906 ----
1907 assert((TRI->getRegSizeInBits(Addr.Base.LoReg, *MRI) == 32 || 0
1908 Addr.Base.LoSubReg) && ----
1909 "Expected 32-bit Base-Register-Low!!"); ----
1910 ----
1911 assert((TRI->getRegSizeInBits(Addr.Base.HiReg, *MRI) == 32 || 0
1912 Addr.Base.HiSubReg) && ----
1913 "Expected 32-bit Base-Register-Hi!!"); ----
1914 ----
1915 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Re-Computed Anchor-Base:\n"); 0
1916 MachineOperand OffsetLo = createRegOrImm(static_cast(Addr.Offset), MI); 0
1917 MachineOperand OffsetHi = ----
1918 createRegOrImm(static_cast(Addr.Offset >> 32), MI); 0
1919 ----
1920 const auto *CarryRC = TRI->getRegClass(AMDGPU::SReg_1_XEXECRegClassID); 0
1921 Register CarryReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(CarryRC); 0
1922 Register DeadCarryReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(CarryRC); 0
1923 ----
1924 Register DestSub0 = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass); 0
1925 Register DestSub1 = MRI->createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass); 0
1926 MachineInstr *LoHalf = ----
1927 BuildMI(*MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e64), DestSub0) 0
1928 .addReg(CarryReg, RegState::Define) 0
1929 .addReg(Addr.Base.LoReg, 0, Addr.Base.LoSubReg) 0
1930 .add(OffsetLo) 0
1931 .addImm(0); // clamp bit 0
1932 (void)LoHalf; ----
1933 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "; LoHalf->dump();); 0
1934 ----
1935 MachineInstr *HiHalf = ----
1936 BuildMI(*MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64), DestSub1) 0
1937 .addReg(DeadCarryReg, RegState::Define | RegState::Dead) 0
1938 .addReg(Addr.Base.HiReg, 0, Addr.Base.HiSubReg) 0
1939 .add(OffsetHi) 0
1940 .addReg(CarryReg, RegState::Kill) 0
1941 .addImm(0); // clamp bit 0
1942 (void)HiHalf; ----
1943 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "; HiHalf->dump();); 0
1944 ----
1945 Register FullDestReg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(TRI->getVGPR64Class()); 0
1946 MachineInstr *FullBase = ----
1947 BuildMI(*MBB, MBBI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::REG_SEQUENCE), FullDestReg) 0
1948 .addReg(DestSub0) 0
1949 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub0) 0
1950 .addReg(DestSub1) 0
1951 .addImm(AMDGPU::sub1); 0
1952 (void)FullBase; ----
1953 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " "; FullBase->dump(); dbgs() << "\n";); 0
1954 ----
1955 return FullDestReg; 0
1956 } 0
1957 ----
1958 // Update base and offset with the NewBase and NewOffset in MI. ----
1959 void SILoadStoreOptimizer::updateBaseAndOffset(MachineInstr &MI, 0
1960 Register NewBase, ----
1961 int32_t NewOffset) const { ----
1962 auto Base = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr); 0
1963 Base->setReg(NewBase); 0
1964 Base->setIsKill(false); 0
1965 TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::offset)->setImm(NewOffset); 0
1966 } 0
1967 ----
1968 std::optional ----
1969 SILoadStoreOptimizer::extractConstOffset(const MachineOperand &Op) const { 0
1970 if (Op.isImm()) 0
1971 return Op.getImm(); 0
1972 ----
1973 if (!Op.isReg()) 0
1974 return std::nullopt; 0
1975 ----
1976 MachineInstr *Def = MRI->getUniqueVRegDef(Op.getReg()); 0
1977 if (!Def || Def->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32 || 0
1978 !Def->getOperand(1).isImm()) 0
1979 return std::nullopt; 0
1980 ----
1981 return Def->getOperand(1).getImm(); 0
1982 } ----
1983 ----
1984 // Analyze Base and extracts: ----
1985 // - 32bit base registers, subregisters ----
1986 // - 64bit constant offset ----
1987 // Expecting base computation as: ----
1988 // %OFFSET0:sgpr_32 = S_MOV_B32 8000 ----
1989 // %LO:vgpr_32, %c:sreg_64_xexec = ----
1990 // V_ADD_CO_U32_e64 %BASE_LO:vgpr_32, %103:sgpr_32, ----
1991 // %HI:vgpr_32, = V_ADDC_U32_e64 %BASE_HI:vgpr_32, 0, killed %c:sreg_64_xexec ----
1992 // %Base:vreg_64 = ----
1993 // REG_SEQUENCE %LO:vgpr_32, %subreg.sub0, %HI:vgpr_32, %subreg.sub1 ----
1994 void SILoadStoreOptimizer::processBaseWithConstOffset(const MachineOperand &Base, 0
1995 MemAddress &Addr) const { ----
1996 if (!Base.isReg()) 0
1997 return; 0
1998 ----
1999 MachineInstr *Def = MRI->getUniqueVRegDef(Base.getReg()); 0
2000 if (!Def || Def->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE 0
2001 || Def->getNumOperands() != 5) 0
2002 return; 0
2003 ----
2004 MachineOperand BaseLo = Def->getOperand(1); 0
2005 MachineOperand BaseHi = Def->getOperand(3); 0
2006 if (!BaseLo.isReg() || !BaseHi.isReg()) 0
2007 return; 0
2008 ----
2009 MachineInstr *BaseLoDef = MRI->getUniqueVRegDef(BaseLo.getReg()); 0
2010 MachineInstr *BaseHiDef = MRI->getUniqueVRegDef(BaseHi.getReg()); 0
2011 ----
2012 if (!BaseLoDef || BaseLoDef->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::V_ADD_CO_U32_e64 || 0
2013 !BaseHiDef || BaseHiDef->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::V_ADDC_U32_e64) 0
2014 return; 0
2015 ----
2016 const auto *Src0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*BaseLoDef, AMDGPU::OpName::src0); 0
2017 const auto *Src1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*BaseLoDef, AMDGPU::OpName::src1); 0
2018 ----
2019 auto Offset0P = extractConstOffset(*Src0); 0
2020 if (Offset0P) 0
2021 BaseLo = *Src1; 0
2022 else { ----
2023 if (!(Offset0P = extractConstOffset(*Src1))) 0
2024 return; 0
2025 BaseLo = *Src0; 0
2026 } ----
2027 ----
2028 Src0 = TII->getNamedOperand(*BaseHiDef, AMDGPU::OpName::src0); 0
2029 Src1 = TII->getNamedOperand(*BaseHiDef, AMDGPU::OpName::src1); 0
2030 ----
2031 if (Src0->isImm()) 0
2032 std::swap(Src0, Src1); 0
2033 ----
2034 if (!Src1->isImm()) 0
2035 return; 0
2036 ----
2037 uint64_t Offset1 = Src1->getImm(); 0
2038 BaseHi = *Src0; 0
2039 ----
2040 Addr.Base.LoReg = BaseLo.getReg(); 0
2041 Addr.Base.HiReg = BaseHi.getReg(); 0
2042 Addr.Base.LoSubReg = BaseLo.getSubReg(); 0
2043 Addr.Base.HiSubReg = BaseHi.getSubReg(); 0
2044 Addr.Offset = (*Offset0P & 0x00000000ffffffff) | (Offset1 << 32); 0
2045 } ----
2046 ----
2047 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::promoteConstantOffsetToImm( 0
2048 MachineInstr &MI, ----
2049 MemInfoMap &Visited, ----
2050 SmallPtrSet &AnchorList) const { ----
2051 ----
2052 if (!(MI.mayLoad() ^ MI.mayStore())) 0
2053 return false; 0
2054 ----
2055 // TODO: Support flat and scratch. ----
2056 if (AMDGPU::getGlobalSaddrOp(MI.getOpcode()) < 0) 0
2057 return false; 0
2058 ----
2059 if (MI.mayLoad() && 0
2060 TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata) != nullptr) 0
2061 return false; 0
2062 ----
2063 if (AnchorList.count(&MI)) 0
2064 return false; 0
2065 ----
2066 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nTryToPromoteConstantOffsetToImmFor "; MI.dump()); 0
2067 ----
2068 if (TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::offset)->getImm()) { 0
2069 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Const-offset is already promoted.\n";); 0
2070 return false; 0
2071 } ----
2072 ----
2073 // Step1: Find the base-registers and a 64bit constant offset. ----
2074 MachineOperand &Base = *TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr); 0
2075 MemAddress MAddr; 0
2076 if (!Visited.contains(&MI)) { 0
2077 processBaseWithConstOffset(Base, MAddr); 0
2078 Visited[&MI] = MAddr; 0
2079 } else ----
2080 MAddr = Visited[&MI]; 0
2081 ----
2082 if (MAddr.Offset == 0) { 0
2083 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " Failed to extract constant-offset or there are no" 0
2084 " constant offsets that can be promoted.\n";); ----
2085 return false; 0
2086 } ----
2087 ----
2088 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " BASE: {" << MAddr.Base.HiReg << ", " 0
2089 << MAddr.Base.LoReg << "} Offset: " << MAddr.Offset << "\n\n";); ----
2090 ----
2091 // Step2: Traverse through MI's basic block and find an anchor(that has the ----
2092 // same base-registers) with the highest 13bit distance from MI's offset. ----
2093 // E.g. (64bit loads) ----
2094 // bb: ----
2095 // addr1 = &a + 4096; load1 = load(addr1, 0) ----
2096 // addr2 = &a + 6144; load2 = load(addr2, 0) ----
2097 // addr3 = &a + 8192; load3 = load(addr3, 0) ----
2098 // addr4 = &a + 10240; load4 = load(addr4, 0) ----
2099 // addr5 = &a + 12288; load5 = load(addr5, 0) ----
2100 // ----
2101 // Starting from the first load, the optimization will try to find a new base ----
2102 // from which (&a + 4096) has 13 bit distance. Both &a + 6144 and &a + 8192 ----
2103 // has 13bit distance from &a + 4096. The heuristic considers &a + 8192 ----
2104 // as the new-base(anchor) because of the maximum distance which can ----
2105 // accommodate more intermediate bases presumably. ----
2106 // ----
2107 // Step3: move (&a + 8192) above load1. Compute and promote offsets from ----
2108 // (&a + 8192) for load1, load2, load4. ----
2109 // addr = &a + 8192 ----
2110 // load1 = load(addr, -4096) ----
2111 // load2 = load(addr, -2048) ----
2112 // load3 = load(addr, 0) ----
2113 // load4 = load(addr, 2048) ----
2114 // addr5 = &a + 12288; load5 = load(addr5, 0) ----
2115 // ----
2116 MachineInstr *AnchorInst = nullptr; 0
2117 MemAddress AnchorAddr; 0
2118 uint32_t MaxDist = std::numeric_limits::min(); 0
2119 SmallVector, 4> InstsWCommonBase; 0
2120 ----
2121 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI.getParent(); 0
2122 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E = MBB->end(); 0
2123 MachineBasicBlock::iterator MBBI = MI.getIterator(); 0
2124 ++MBBI; 0
2125 const SITargetLowering *TLI = ----
2126 static_cast(STM->getTargetLowering()); 0
2127 ----
2128 for ( ; MBBI != E; ++MBBI) { 0
2129 MachineInstr &MINext = *MBBI; 0
2130 // TODO: Support finding an anchor(with same base) from store addresses or ----
2131 // any other load addresses where the opcodes are different. ----
2132 if (MINext.getOpcode() != MI.getOpcode() || 0
2133 TII->getNamedOperand(MINext, AMDGPU::OpName::offset)->getImm()) 0
2134 continue; 0
2135 ----
2136 const MachineOperand &BaseNext = ----
2137 *TII->getNamedOperand(MINext, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr); 0
2138 MemAddress MAddrNext; 0
2139 if (!Visited.contains(&MINext)) { 0
2140 processBaseWithConstOffset(BaseNext, MAddrNext); 0
2141 Visited[&MINext] = MAddrNext; 0
2142 } else ----
2143 MAddrNext = Visited[&MINext]; 0
2144 ----
2145 if (MAddrNext.Base.LoReg != MAddr.Base.LoReg || 0

2428 bool SILoadStoreOptimizer::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
2429 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 0
2430 return false; 0
2431 ----
2432 STM = &MF.getSubtarget(); 0
2433 if (!STM->loadStoreOptEnabled()) 0
2434 return false; 0
2435 ----
2436 TII = STM->getInstrInfo(); 0
2437 TRI = &TII->getRegisterInfo(); 0
2438 ----
2439 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
2440 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
2441 ----
2442 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Running SILoadStoreOptimizer\n"); 0
2443 ----
2444 bool Modified = false; 0
2445 ----
2446 // Contains the list of instructions for which constant offsets are being ----
2447 // promoted to the IMM. This is tracked for an entire block at time. ----
2448 SmallPtrSet AnchorList; 0
2449 MemInfoMap Visited; 0
2450 ----
2451 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) { 0
2452 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SectionEnd; 0
2453 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB.begin(), E = MBB.end(); I != E; 0
2454 I = SectionEnd) { 0
2455 bool CollectModified; ----
2456 std::list> MergeableInsts; 0
2457 ----
2458 // First pass: Collect list of all instructions we know how to merge in a ----
2459 // subset of the block. ----
2460 std::tie(SectionEnd, CollectModified) = 0
2461 collectMergeableInsts(I, E, Visited, AnchorList, MergeableInsts); 0
2462 ----
2463 Modified |= CollectModified; 0
2464 ----
2465 do { ----
2466 OptimizeAgain = false; 0
2467 Modified |= optimizeBlock(MergeableInsts); 0
2468 } while (OptimizeAgain); 0
2469 } 0
2470 ----
2471 Visited.clear(); 0
2472 AnchorList.clear(); 0
2473 } ----
2474 ----
2475 return Modified; 0
2476 } 0
